{"lemma":"مُدُودِ","slug":"مُدُودِ","root":"م.د.د","root_slug":"م-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/م-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَدّ","root":"مدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13379","n13381"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to extend, to stretch, to spread out, to lay out","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"اُمْدُدْ يَدَكَ / مُدَّ يَدَكَ.","english":"Extend your hand."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to help, to support","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to supply, to provide","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of مَدَّ (madda) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flow of the sea, rising tide (when the ebb has ceased)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a dry measure varying in size by several liters","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare مَتَّ (matta) and مَطَّ (maṭṭa). Cognate with Akkadian 𒉘 (madādum, “to measure”).\n\nProbably via Aramaic 𐡬𐡣𐡩𐡠 (mdyʾ) / מוֹדְיָא (moḏyā) / ܡܘܿܕܝܳܐ (moḏyā) from Akkadian 𒉘𒈨𒌍 (/⁠maddattu, middattu⁠/, “a measure of capacity for dates, water, and other things; a vessel”), whence also Ancient Greek μόδιος (módios) and Latin modius. Take the rarer volume measure names Arabic مُدْي (mudy) and Old Armenian մոդ (mod) into account."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13379","headword_ar":"مَدُودٌ","root":"dwd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next precedes."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13381","headword_ar":"مُدَوِّدٌ","root":"dwd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what ne